{
  "stem": "1338.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in the last few weeks in Auschwitz, there were weeks, there were days, where I thought that it would be just as well if I just-- if I only had the courage to take that thermometer, or whatever means to do that.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, I felt that-- but there were days, of course, which were different.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But, yes, I was-- I had a big scar here on my thing, which never healed until I-- the war ended, and I got food and you know-- I got good food.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, of course, it naturally healed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I have had a scar here where I was beaten by somebody into the mud.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I got terrible pus here and I couldn't move.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, during the time when they took us out from Auschwitz, you know, they had selection, who is going to be shipped out, and they want to make sure that you have any diseases, so, you know, like all kinds of infectious disease.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They would make you lower the pants to see whether you have any, you know, pimples or anything on your body.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I lowered them right up to here, up to the knee.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If I have lowered it below knee, I would-- I would obviously be selected not to go to another camp, in other words, to leave Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, yes, I would say that Auschwitz was probably the closest that I have been to being completely-- I presume my mother was not alive anymore.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I- I didn't really see that as- as-- as a way of going on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so, yes, that probably was the most critical time, where I really was ready to kind of, you know, yes or no.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
